so we dont expose Ingress YAML as svc right?

Correct! Ingress YAML is NOT a Service — it is just a rules document.

Ingress YAML = Menu in a restaurant
               lists what's available
               where things go
               BUT menu itself is not the door ❌

Ingress YAML is never exposed as a service — it is just a rulebook. The controller reads the rulebook and the actual exposure happens via ALB (ALB Controller) or NGINX Controller Service (NGINX Controller).

ALB Controller:
  1 LB = ALB              → directly routes to pods
  Simpler ✅

NGINX Controller:
  1 LB = NLB/Classic      → goes to NGINX pod
  1 NGINX pod             → routes to your pods
  Two hops ⚠️
  More control ✅


