Ingress YAML is waht?

Ingress YAML is a Kubernetes resource that defines routing rules — how external traffic reaches your services inside the cluster.

Simple meaning:

Ingress YAML = Traffic rulebook

Rules like:
  myapp.com/api   → send to api-service
  myapp.com/web   → send to web-service
  admin.myapp.com → send to admin-service

Path vs Host routing:

# Path based routing
host: myapp.com
  /api  → api-service
  /web  → web-service
  /db   → db-service

# Host based routing
api.myapp.com   → api-service
web.myapp.com   → web-service
admin.myapp.com → admin-service

Interview Answer:

"Ingress is a Kubernetes resource that defines routing rules for external traffic. Instead of creating a separate LoadBalancer for every service, you create one Ingress with rules like host-based or path-based routing to direct traffic to the right service. The Ingress resource itself does nothing — it needs a controller like ALB Controller or NGINX Controller to read the rules and implement them."


