so we cant use one ALB for 400 deployment?

Great question! Technically you CAN use one ALB for 400 services — but there are limits!

One ALB for 400 Services — The Problem

ALB has hard limits:

Listener rules per ALB  → max 100 rules (default)
                           max 300 rules (after limit increase)
Target Groups per ALB   → max 100 (default)

Your company has 400+ services
→ 400 rules needed
→ exceeds ALB limits ❌

What You Can Do with One ALB

Option 1: Request limit increase from AWS
  default  : 100 rules
  max limit: 300 rules  ← still not enough for 400+ ❌

Option 2: Use multiple ALBs
  ALB 1 → services 1-100
  ALB 2 → services 101-200
  ALB 3 → services 201-300
  ALB 4 → services 301-400
  4 ALBs × $20 = $80/month
  Still cheaper than 400 ALBs ✅
  But complex to manage ❌

